5:
97, 98, 99... I didn't realize I'd painted
so many already. Only one more to
go...
9:
Just one last painting... But what
should it be of?
18:
It's been a while, Kugui. How are you
faring?
23:
Ch-Chairman! I'm fine, thank you,
but... What are you doing in Starview?
26:
I've come to assign you a job, I'm
afraid.
28:
There's been a minor incident, and I
need your expertise in order to
identify a cursed painting inside a
haunted house.
32:
A cursed painting inside a haunted
house? Are you chasing the origins
of a rumor or something?
36:
If only it were so benign.
The other day, an art dealer
involved in illegal trading was
apprehended, and his entire
collection is... unpleasant, to say the
least.
38:
The storeroom is filled with so many
cursed paintings, it's impossible to
locate the main source causing the
haunting.
42: I see... That's where I come in.
45:
Indeed. I apologize for bothering you
during your vacation, but I could
truly use your assistance.
50: You will have it. I won't let you down!
57:
A depiction of a decapitated
criminal... A frame of a warrior
stabbing himself...
61:
I won't claim to understand... but I
suppose this is art in someone else's
eyes.
66:
There's no accounting for taste... It
certainly isn't for me, though.
70:
But if I had continued down the path
I used to be onâ€”
74:
This painting... At first glance it
appears to be nothing more than a
beautiful portrait, but it's
enshrouded by a powerful curse.
78:
Is that our source, then? I'm
surprised such an ordinary picture
could be the culprit.
82:
Chairman, please erect a barrier
around myself and the painting.
I need to concentrate...
91:
No... It hurts. It HURTS! Why are you
doing this to me... WHY?!
94:
...That would explain the strength of
the curse.
97:
He killed her, then used her blood to
paint the portrait... How horrible.
100:
Hehe... This is true art! Pure... ART! I
must PAINT!
106:
Blood... More blood. Kill... Kill... KILL!
Hehe, there is nothing more pure...
more BEAUTIFUL!
109:
I could have become like you, at one
point.
112:
But that future never came to pass...
and it never will.
115:
I have found my path.
Devour him.
122:
It hurts... Hurts so much! Somebody,
save me...
125:
It's all right... Everything will be fine
now.
130:
She woke up in perfect health, or so I
believed... What is she doing?
133:
I'm not sure... But I suspect we'll find
out soon enough.
137:
Here you are. A portrait with no
scars... no blood. A depiction of you
as you once were.
140:
You were so beautiful.
I promise, there will be no more pain.
147:
Well done, Kugui.
I'm curious... What compelled you to
paint her?
151: It just... felt like the right thing to do.
154:
So I followed my instinct, and did
what I could.
161:
...This is quite a painting.
Did something happen? Your brush
strokes are far more patient here.
165:
Yes... I realized a truth that was right
in front of me this whole time.
167:
Ryouki and I... Even if we're aiming
for the same ideal, both our reasons
for painting and our styles are
different.
170:
I have my own approach, and it's
fine to stay true to it. That's what
everyone on my journey helped me
see.
184:
Is that all you have to say?! You run
off without a word, and you don't
even tell Master where you've gone...
187:
I even went to my parents and
asked them to help me search for
you! Do you have any idea how
worried I was?!
196:
Don't think you can charm your way
out of this!
201:
By the way, Ryouki. There's
somewhere I'd like to take you, when
you have the time.
205:
Huh? Where do you wanna go? Is it
one of those places you went to
train?
210:
Yes... There's so much to see, and so
many people to meet. I think you'll
be pleasantly surprised.
